  "text": "For the drought stress treatment, water was withheld for 2 weeks from 3-week-old plants with similar size grown under normal conditions in soil in a growth room, afterwards, rewatering was applied and survival rates were measured 3 days after rewatering. For water loss rate assays, leaves were detached from 4-week-old plants grown under normal conditions, and placed on filter paper at room temperature for 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 h, and then fresh weights of the leaves at each time point were measured as described previously [CITATION_1] . Three independent experiments were performed.",
